<article id="post-10427" class="post-10427 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-computerhardware category-technology tag-moranbong-game-console">
	<header class="entry-header clearfix">
		<h1 class="entry-title">
			Moranbong motion-based video games system		</h1>
		<div class="entry-tags clearfix"><span>TOPICS:</span><a href="https://www.northkoreatech.org/tag/moranbong-game-console/" rel="tag">Moranbong game console</a></div>	</header>
	
<div class="entry-thumbnail">
<img width="400" height="246" src="https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image1.jpg" class="attachment-content-single size-content-single wp-post-image" alt="" srcset="https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image1.jpg 400w, https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image1-200x123.jpg 200w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></div>
		<p class="entry-meta">
<span class="entry-meta-author vcard author">Posted By: <a class="fn" href="https://www.northkoreatech.org/author/martynw/">Martyn Williams</a></span>
<span class="entry-meta-date updated">September 10, 2019</span>
</p>
	<div class="entry-content clearfix">
		
<div class="twitter-share"><a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.northkoreatech.org%2F2019%2F09%2F10%2Fmoranbong-motion-based-video-games-system%2F&#038;via=northkoreatech" class="twitter-share-button">Tweet</a></div>
<p>North Korea appears to have developed its own version of the Nintendo Wii. The Moranbong games console comes with a couple of motion-sensitive controllers and a sensor bar that includes a camera.</p>
<p>It was briefly detailed by the state-run Arirang Meari website on Monday with a few small images of the device.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10430" src="https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image1.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="246" srcset="https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image1.jpg 400w, https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image1-200x123.jpg 200w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>
<p>Through the console, users can experience various physical activities that are good for physical fitness, obesity, and whole body, the report said.</p>
<p>It highlighted a shooting game and a running game that appears to use a floor mat as part of the system. These are all similar components to those offered with the Nintendo Wii and PlayStation Move.</p>
<p>Arirang Meari didn&#8217;t disclose any details about the manufacturer of the device. It&#8217;s possible the device was developed in North Korea although it&#8217;s much more likely that it has been acquired from a Chinese electronics maker and branded with the Moranbong name.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10429" src="https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image2.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="335" srcset="https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image2.jpg 400w, https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image2-200x168.jpg 200w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-10428" src="https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image3.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="279" srcset="https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image3.jpg 400w, https://www.northkoreatech.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/news_2019-09-09_32634_image3-200x140.jpg 200w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>
	</div>
